BFN 

  [Text] The great leader Comrade Kim Il-song sent a message 
of greetings to Boris Nikolayevich Yeltsin on the Russian 
national day. 
  The message reads: 
  Moscow, Your Excellency Boris Nikolayevich Yeltsin, 
president 
of the Russian Federation: 
  I congratulate you and the Russian people on the Russian 
national day. I take this opportunity to express the belief 
that relations between the peoples of our two countries will 
develop on the principle of independence, equality, and 
non-interference in other's internal affairs. 
  [Signed] Kim Il-song, DPRK president 
  [Dated] 11 June 1994, Pyongyang 

